r', sketching changing norms around the familial control of women from agrarian/pastoral roots to the contemporary era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFamily violencezIraqzKurdistān. 0aFamily violencezIraqzKurdistān. 0aHonor killingszIraqzKurdistān. 0aHonor killingszIraqzKurdistān. 0aKinshipzIraqzKurdistān. 0aKinshipzIraqzKurdistān. 0aMarriagexEconomic aspectszIraqzKurdistān. 0aMarriagexEconomic aspectszIraqzKurdistān. 0aWomen, KurdishxViolence againstzIraqzKurdistān. 0aWomen, KurdishxViolence againstzIraqzKurdistān. 0aWomen, KurdishzIraqzKurdistānxSocial conditions. 0aWomen, KurdishzIraqzKurdistānxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aMarriage, politics, violence against women, gender, Kurdistan region of Iraq, Iraq, honor, honor crimes, women, girls, female sexual autonomy, moral codes, violence against girls, social taboos, sexuality, Kurdish women, feminism, Kurdish feminists, Kurdish communities, history, anthropology, Middle Eastern studies, anthropology of the family, honor killings, family structure, violence, Kurdistan.1 aBerta, Péter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhan, Deeyah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhan, Deeyah.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069033040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978801752?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978801752423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978801752/original  a978-3-11-069033-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE